...but what can you do?
但你能做什么？

19
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:14,040
I worry about the children.
我担心孩子

20
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:16,560
My invoice is in the envelope,
if that's all.
如果没有别的事
我的账单在信封内

21
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:19,320
Yes, Mr. Welles. Thank you.
好，谢谢你，魏斯先生

22
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:23,400
Let me know if I can be of
further assistance to you, Senator.
如果我还有什么可以帮忙
请随时与我联络，参议员

23
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,240
保持联络
I'll be in touch.

24
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,200
有人吗？
Hello?

25
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:06,200
你回来了
You're home.

26
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:08,520
我们在这里
We're back here.

27
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:10,600
一切顺利吗？
How did it go?

28
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:11,920
还不错吧
I think very well.

29
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,440
很好
Good.

30
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,600
甜心，爹地回来了
Daddy's home, sweetie.

31
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:18,960
你教科书工作如何？
How's the textbook business?

32
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:23,320
那个联邦剧场的方案
我收到一万字
I got 1 0,000 words on
the federal theatre project.

33
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:26,960
应该只有四千字
但作者拒绝修改
It should be 4,000 and the writer
doesn't want to change anything.

34
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,440
所以有点麻烦
So kind of bad.

35
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:31,440
迈阿密怎样？
How was Miami?

36
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:33,200
不错，只是寂寞
Fine. Lonesome.

37
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:35,360
就算付我很多钱
我也不要住在那
Couldn't pay me enough
to live down there.

38
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:37,280
那你为什么去？
Then why'd you go?

39
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:40,880
麦可孙议员有很多
有势力的朋友
Senator Michaelson has
powerful friends.

40
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:48,720
哈，仙蒂
Hello, Cinderella.

41
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,480
想我吗？我好想你
Did you miss me?
I sure missed you.

42
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:53,320
-她很想你
-这才对
-She missed you.
-That's my girl.

43
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:55,880
她想你，我也想你
She missed you.
I missed you.

44
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,640
你吸烟？
You been smoking?

45
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,920
吸烟？ 我没有吸烟
Smoking? I'm not smoking.

46
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:04,880
别这样，蜜糖儿
Come on, honey.

47
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:07,120
你一身的烟味
You reek of it.

48
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:10,760
艾美，我坐在酒吧内
跟踪那男人
Amy, I've been sitting around
in bars following this guy.

49
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,840
这就是你给我的见面礼？
Is this the first thing I get?

50
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:15,760
-你在指责我吗？
-我没有指责你
-You're accusing me?
-I'm not accusing you.

51
00:05:16,760 --> 00:05:19,680
我没有吸烟，好不好？
我们以前就讲过了
I'm not smoking, okay?
We've been all through that.

52
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:22,920
我去弄晚餐，你肚子饿吗？
I'll make dinner.
Are you hungry?

53
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,160
你烧饭？
You're cooking?

54
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,920
我想你
I missed you.

55
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:38,440
我不喜欢你不在家
I don't like it when you leave.

56
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:44,680
该我去吗？
Should I go?

57
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:46,760
我去吧
I'm going to do it.

58
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:59,800
来吧
Come on.

59
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:02,800
有什么事，仙蒂？
What's all the trouble, Cinderella?

60
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:05,120
乖，乖
There, there.

61
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,480
我爱你
I love you.

62
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,320
我爱你
I love you.

63
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:36,080
蜜糖儿，电话
Honey, phone!

64
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:46,400
好，我在听
Okay, I've got it!

65
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:49,320
对不起，我正在换电话
Sorry, I was just switching phones.

66
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:55,680
我很荣幸认识你，龙雕先生
It's a pleasure to make
your acquaintance, Mr. Longdale.

67
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:58,080
我有什么能为你效劳？
How can I be of assistance to you?

68
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:05,440
四点整没问题
Four o'clock would be fine.

69
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:11,520
我想我知道在那里
I think I know where it is.

70
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:55,160
魏斯先生，我是丹尼龙雕
我们通过电话
Mr. Welles, Daniel Longdale.
We spoke on the phone.

71
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:56,160
你好
Pleasure.

72
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:59,480
我是柯立斯纯家族的律师和
财产处理人
I'm the Christians' attorney and
one of the executors of the estate.

73
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:00,800
这位是柯太太
This is Mrs. Christian.

74
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:02,800
很荣幸认识你，夫人
It's an honour to meet you, ma'am.

75
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:05,560
魏斯先生，你有很高的评价
You come highly recommended,
Mr. Welles.

76
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:09,640
我和我在哈里斯堡，兰卡士达
以及荷西的合伙人谈过
I've spoken to assoclates of mine in
Harrisburg and Lancaster and Hershey.

77
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:11,480
你认识很多有影响力的人物
You have influential friends.

78
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:14,760
我很庆幸可以为我崇拜的人
提供服务
I've been privileged to provide
services for people I admire.

79
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:17,400
你的谨慎被赞赏
You were praised
for your discretion...

80
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:20,920
还有你能保守秘密
...your strict adherence
to confidentiality.

81
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,080
谢谢你，夫人
Thank you, ma'am.

82
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:28,360
你知道，我丈夫最近逝世
As you know,
my husband passed away recently.

83
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,840
请节哀，夫人
My condolences, Mrs. Christian.

84
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:34,600
他的离开留给我….
His passing has left me...

85
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:36,360
一些需要解决的事
...with a dilemma.

86
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,680
我会尽力帮忙
I'll do whatever I can to help.

87
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:42,000
这是我丈夫的私人书房
My husband's inner sanctum.

88
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:44,680
没有什么人曾经进入这房内
Not many people have been
inside this room.

89
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:49,200
我父亲在匹兹堡钢铁场工作
My father worked the Pittsburgh mill.

90
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:51,680
我相信是尔稳联合钢铁
Irving United Steel, I believe.

91
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:54,360
但你拿到宾州大学奖学金
But you attended Penn
on an academic scholarship.

92
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:55,680
没错
That's right.

93
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:58,440
你同学都念法律和财经
而你选择侦探学
Peers went into law and finance,
but you chose surveillance.

94
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,520
我知道那才是将来
I decided it was the future.

95
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:02,360
你丈夫是个传奇
Your husband is a legend.

96
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,720
请坐
Please.

97
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:06,440
我们结婚四十五年
We were married 45 years.

98
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:09,960
四个儿女，七个孙子
Four children, seven grandchildren.

99
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:12,200
但他真正醉心的
But his true passion lay...

100
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,680
是他的工作
...in his work.

101
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:15,760
但他一直很忠心
But he was always loyal.

102
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:17,440
我非常地
I loved him...

103
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,040
深爱他
...deeply.

104
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:20,880
我明白
I understand.

105
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,640
丹尼
Daniel.

106
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:29,040
只有我丈夫一人知道
这保险箱的密码
My husband was the only one with
the combination to this safe.

107
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,880
我们请人把它打开
We had to hire somebody to open it.

108
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:33,400
我避免让任何人
I prevented anyone...

109
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,720
看保险箱内的东西
...from seeing the contents.

110
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:39,080
我觉得那是我丈夫的私人物品
I felt these were
my husband's private things.

111
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,360
我没有…..
I didn't....

112
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:44,240
我没有察觉….
I didn't realize....

113
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:47,480
你想告诉我发现什么吗？
Do you want to tell me
what you found?

114
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:52,120
现金，股票
Cash, stock certificates.

115
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:56,600
没有什么不寻常，真的，除了….
Nothing out of the ordinary,
really, except that.

116
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:59,600
一套短片
It's a film...

117
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,920
好像有个少女被杀
...where a girl appears to be murdered.

118
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:05,920
我不肯定我明白
I'm not sure I understand.

119
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:07,760
拍的很真实
It's very realistic.

120
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:11,280
但每天有多少人在电影或电视上
But how many people seem to be
realistically killed...

121
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:13,280
好像真的被杀害
in movies and on TV every day?

122
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:17,760
开始时像一套低俗的色情电影
It begins as a relatively
sleazy bit of pornography...

123
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:21,040
但突然变的很暴力和血腥
...and rapidly turns
quite violent and bloody.

124
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:29,120
你所说的叫色情暴力电影
What you're talking about
is called a snuff film.

125
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,600
照我所知，色情暴力电影
是都市神话
From what I know,
snuff films are an urban myth.

126
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:35,200
性行业的传说，根本没有这回事
Sex industry folklore.
There's no such thing.

127
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:37,280
我也这样向柯太太解释
That's what I explained
to Mrs. Christian.

128
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:40,040
这可能是一些性虐待的电影
This is probably
an S & M film of some sort.

129
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:42,200
模拟强奸，模拟暴力
Simulated rape, simulated violence.

130
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:44,720
令人倒胃口，但都是拍出来的
It's hard to stomach,
but there are ways of doing it.

131
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:46,520
假血浆，特别效果
Fake blood, special effects.

132
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:49,920
请你看完这影片后
告诉我你的意见
Would you look at the film
and give us your opinion?

133
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:51,800
我只希望
All I want...

134
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:56,240
知道这暴行是假的
...is to know that
this atrocity is false.

135
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:58,560
我要证据
I want the proof.

136
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:54,760
嗯….
Well...

137
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:58,080
拍这电影的人拍的非常传神
...whoever made the film was adept
at authenticity.

138
00:12:58,240 --> 00:13:01,920
我不是专家，我提议
让警方去决定
But I'm no expert. I suggest letting
the police make a determination.

139
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:03,080
不可能
Out of the question.

140
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:06,000
有几个原因说明这是不必要
That would be so unnecessary
for any number of reasons...

141
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:09,440
不单只是为了柯先生的名誉
...not the least of which is
Mr. Christian's reputation.

142
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,000
我们只想你找出拍这套影片的人
We want you to find out
who made this film...

143
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:15,040
证实这是真是假
...and establish whether it's real.

144
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:16,840
你可以开个价钱
You can name your price.

145
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:20,840
我们会供应
你买资料用的任何资源
You'll be provided with whatever
you need to buy information.

146
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,120
那少女是唯一的线索
Girl's all I've got to go on.

147
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:27,120
我可以当它是
一宗人口失踪案件
I could treat it
like a missing persons case.

148
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:28,280
明白
Understood.

149
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:29,520
当然….
Of course...

150
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:33,440
我们要确保你不会拷贝这套影片
...we need to be assured
that you would not copy this film.

151
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:35,520
我向你保证
You have my word on that.

152
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:37,960
我只向你汇报
But I'll be dealing
directly with you...

153
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:39,120
只向你一个
...and only you.

154
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,280
你与你律师的关系如何
是你的事
Your relationship with
your attorney is your own.

155
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:43,480
-不是对你不礼貌
-不会
-No offense.
-None taken.

156
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:46,960
我觉得你已经详细的考虑过
I realize you've given this
careful consideration.

157
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:49,880
你可以毁灭它
You could have destroyed it.

158
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:52,720
告诉我这可怜的少女没有被杀
Tell me the poor girl wasn't killed.

159
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:54,240
求你
Please?

160
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:56,400
找到她，要活着的
Find her alive.

161
00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:58,720
我会尽力，夫人
I'll do the best I can, ma'am.

162
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:41,000
你要去克利夫兰？
Cleveland?

163
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:42,200
你刚到家
You just got home.

164
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:45,200
我也希望可以留下
但这是房子的贷款
And I wish I could stay,
but this is the mortgage.

165
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,920
仙蒂上大学的学费
It's Cindy's college money.

166
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:49,360
如果我办好这事
凭柯太太的社交圈子
If I do right by her,
with the circle she runs in...

167
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,040
这会是一个难得的机会
...this could be a big break.

168
00:14:51,280 --> 00:14:52,680
我不认为我们需要什么机会
I didn't know we needed a break.

169
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,960
你父亲认为我们需要
Your father seems to think we do.

170
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:00,800
那，柯太太是怎样的人？
So, what was Mrs. Christian like?

171
00:15:00,960 --> 00:15:04,440
就像你所想像的
我为她感到难过
Like you'd expect, I guess.
I feel sorry for her.

172
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,720
那是宗人口失踪案
It's a missing persons.

173
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:08,720
我告诉她我会用两至三周时间
I told her I'd give it
a couple, three weeks.

174
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:12,360
不该会用更多的时间
成功的机会不大
It can't take longer than that.
It's an outside shot.

175
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:16,720
我只能告诉你这么多
你最好不要知道那么多
That's all I can tell you. Sometimes
you can't know what I'm doing.

176
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:19,200
常常是这样
It's always that way.

177
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:21,960
她醒了，我去看她
She's awake. I'll get her.

178
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:23,960
好吧，我很快会上去
All right, I'll be up in a sec.

179
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:54,920
-你带枪？
-我不需要它
-You're taking the gun?
-I won't need it.

180
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:56,000
那不要带
Don't take it.

181
00:15:56,160 --> 00:15:57,920
我不会用它，这只是作预防
I won't wear it.
It's just a precaution.

182
00:15:58,160 --> 00:15:59,000
别担心
